Hi team,

I’m looking for some support, specifically around the API / python SDK.

We’re using the python SDK to create contacts in HubSpot since our server is where we have all the contextual information about our contacts. I am trying to find a way, however, to send the HubSpot user token (stored in a cookie) which contains the information about any ads the user may have navigated to the platform via. As far as I can tell, there is no way for me to do this and the only way to add the HubSpot user token is by identifying the contact via the javascript client. I am hoping that this is not the case and I am missing something obvious in the documentation so hopefully you can point me at that.

If it’s helpful, here is the code we’re using the python SDK to create the contact.

```    def create_contact(self, user: FFAdminUser, HubSpot_company_id: str) -&gt; dict:
        properties = {
            "email": user.email,
            "firstname": user.first_name,
            "lastname": user.last_name,
            "hs_marketable_status": user.marketing_consent_given,
        }

        response = self.client.crm.contacts.basic_api.create(
            simple_public_object_input_for_create=SimplePublicObjectInputForCreate(
                properties=properties,
                associations=[
                    {
                        "types": [
                            {
                                "associationCategory": "HubSpot_DEFINED",
                                "associationTypeId": 1,
                            }
                        ],
                        "to": {"id": HubSpot_company_id},
                    }
                ],
            )
        )
        return response.to_dict()```
